body.body: option is added to the Main Menu on the instruments when your dealer configures your motorcycle after fitting the My Triumph Connectivity Module.
Push button/joystick down to highlight the
Press button/joystick centre to select the
The menu allows access to the following options:

This option provides an alphanumeric keyboard through which you can access contacts stored in the connected phone. You use the buttons/joystick to enter the initial character(s) of the name for which you want to search and to select a contact from the resulting list. The resulting list can be also scrolled through using the buttons/joystick.

This option provides a numeric keyboard through which you can enter a number to dial on the connected phone. You use the buttons/joystick to enter the number that you want to dial and to make the call.

This option determines whether the My Triumph Connectivity Module accepts incoming calls automatically or waits for you to accept, reject or ignore them. Depending on phone settings, rejected calls are redirected to voicemail.
This option determines whether music is played repeatedly and, if so, whether the track or the whole album/playlist is repeated.
This option determines whether tracks are played in the sequence held on the media player or in a random sequence.
This option starts a search for
-enabled devices within range, creating a list from which devices can be selected. The search can be stopped at any time. You use the buttons/joystick to select a device to pair.
This option lists the paired devices associated with the rider. A 'tick' is shown next to the currently connected device.
This option lists the paired devices associated with the passenger. A 'tick' is shown next to the currently connected device.
This option lists paired devices, which can then be unpaired individually or collectively.
This option lists the different types of
-related notifications, which can then be displayed or hidden as preferred:

This option provides a keyboard through which you can specify a name for the My Triumph Connectivity Module fitted to your motorcycle. This is the name that will be displayed by paired devices, such as your phone.
The name must contain at least four characters.
options is the same as the one used to enter your name for the
option on the Display Setup Menu. Refer to the Owner’s Handbook for your motorcycle for more information.
